6:
One toy per person, everyone! And
behave, all right? No roughhousing!
11:
Looks like the toys are hit. We
knocked it out of the park, didn't we,
Adonis?
18:
Hey, Mister... Did you pick these toys
for us?
20: That's right. Do you like them?
28: Take good care of them, then.
34: Adonis, do you have a moment?
49:
Ever since we went to the
orphanage, something about you
has seemed off. I was merely
worried.
52:
If you ever have any concerns or
problems, feel—
56:
I have no need for counselling. I'm
perfectly capable of managing my
own emotions.
59:
I see. Well, regardless, if anything
were to come up, I don't want you to
have any reservations about
approaching us.
62:
All the people who live here in
Starview Village... We're something
like family to each other.
65:
Listen, Adonis... We're a family, all
right?
67:
The roof over your head, your
clothes, food—I provide all of these
things for you.
69:
So in return, I want you to listen to
what I say, okay? You're my son.
73:
I need you to be good for me, okay?
To be as beautiful as possible.
77:
Heh. People really are so easily
manipulated...
87:
I'm sorry. I'm afraid this type of
conversation isn't to my liking.
97:
I fear I might have overstepped... I
should have chosen my words more
carefully.
104:
What have I done to warrant being
followed, I wonder?
108:
Nothing, I assume. That wasn't my
intention.
110:
I was just thinking about the
orphanage today, about all those
presents we gave away. I wanted to
talk to you about it.
114: Feel free to do so, then.
118:
Well, I was surprised to find we were
quite under budget. We didn't spend
that much after all.
121:
Likely because we put in the effort of
adjusting all those toys by
hand—being frugal often comes at
the cost of time.
125:
How did other people handle this in
the past? Did they just run out of
money and leave some kids without
presents?
128:
When those in charge are careless
in their duty, that's precisely what
happens.
136:
When there aren't enough presents,
it becomes a free-for-all.
138:
The strongest kids get a toy—the
weakest ones are left to cry
themselves to sleep.
142:
You put in a lot of effort to make
sure that didn't happen this time,
huh?
145:
Because the Guild expressly hired
me to do so. I merely acted out of
self-interest.
149:
Maybe. But I know for a fact the kids
loved the presents.
152:
Children are innocent. They can't yet
see what really happens behind the
scenes. What truly motivates people.
158:
I never thought myself the present-
giving type. Yet here I am.
162:
I think it's about time I retire for the
night. I'll find time to make amends
to Light at some point in the future.
